Annotations.Contents: IMPORTANT NOTE ABOUT THIS PAGE: This page was created for the testing the display of link annotation parameters. The file was created using Adobe Acrobat 5.0 (and modified using Acrobat 6.0). The displaying of each annotation is specified in the annotation. By default, Acrobat sets link annotations so that they are normally displayed by 'viewer' applications. They are not normally displayed in printed output. That is the case with these annotations.Ghostscript checks the display specifications for each annotation. By default, Ghostscript assumes that the output is 'printed' if the 'OutputFile' parameter is defined. Adding '-dPrinted=false' to the command line will force Ghostscript to display 'viewer' annotations in all output. Adding '-dPrinted=true' will disable the displaying of these annotations.
